Seafood Fried Rice Recipe

Ingredients:
1 plate cooked white rice
100 g seafood (shrimp, squid, or mix)
2 cloves garlic (minced)
1 egg
2 tbsp sweet soy sauce
Salt & pepper to taste
Cooking oil

Instructions:
Heat oil, sauté garlic until fragrant, add seafood and cook through.
Push to the side, scramble the egg.
Add rice and mix well.
Season with soy sauce, salt, and pepper.
Stir until evenly heated, then serve.
